# Python Version & venv

Key lessons:
    Virtual environments (venv) isolate project dependencies from the global Python environment.
    Without activating a venv â†’ Python uses the global environment.
    venvs are locked to the Python version used to create them. You cannot upgrade Python inside an existing venv.


Steps to use venv properly:

    Install the desired Python version on your system.
    Create a venv using that version:
    python3.11 -m venv venv
Activate the venv:
    .\venv\Scripts\activate
Install project dependencies:
    pip install requests transformers torch
Deactivate with:
    deactivate